e thesis, therefore, underlines the conspicuous differences between the Thessalonian and Corinthian congregations concerning their socio-economic compositions, social relationships, and further social identities, while extrapolating certain circles of causality between them through socio-economic and social-scientific criticism. This study concludes Paul’s teachings of grace, community, and ethics were manifested and modified in different communities in different ways because of these different socio-economic contexts.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aChristianity and culturezRome. 0aChurch historyyca. 30-100. 0aSocial classes in the Bible. 4aFrühchristentum. 4aPaulus. 4aSozialwissenschaften. 7aRELIGION / Biblical Studies / New Testament.2bisacsh  a1 Corinthians.  a1 Thessalonians.  aDifferences between the Pauline congregations.  aSocial Psychological approach.  aSocial history of the Pauline church.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package English 2021z978311075072008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2021 Part 1z978311075070608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2021 Englishz978311075419308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2021z9783110753974oZDB-23-DGF0 cEPUBz97831107425890 cprintz978311074201540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311074244240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110742442423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110742442/original  a978-3-11-07507